Here's how to implement all three:

### 1. Custom "Cancel" Back Button (EditProductPage.xaml)

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.EditProductPage">
    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior TextOverride="Cancel"
                           Command="{Binding CancelCommand}" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
    <!-- your form content -->
</ContentPage>
```

The `Command` on `BackButtonBehavior` **replaces** the default back navigation, so you control what happens:

```csharp
// In your ViewModel
[RelayCommand]
async Task Cancel()
{
    if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        bool discard = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "You have unsaved changes. Discard them?",
            "Discard", "Stay");
        if (!discard) return;
    }
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
}
```

### 2. Guard the Hardware/Swipe Back (AppShell.xaml.cs)

The `BackButtonBehavior.Command` only intercepts the **toolbar** back button. To also catch the Android hardware back button or iOS swipe-back gesture, add a navigation guard in `AppShell`:

```csharp
protected override async void OnNavigating(ShellNavigatingEventArgs args)
{
    base.OnNavigating(args);

    // Only intercept back navigation from EditProductPage
    if (args.Source == ShellNavigationSource.Pop
        && Shell.Current.CurrentPage is EditProductPage page
        && page.HasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        var deferral = args.GetDeferral();

        bool discard = await page.DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "You have unsaved changes. Discard them?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (!discard)
            args.Cancel();

        deferral.Complete();
    }
}
```

**Key points:**
- **`GetDeferral()`** is required because `DisplayAlert` is async — without it the navigation completes before the dialog returns.
- **`args.Cancel()`** stops the navigation if the user picks "Stay".
- **`deferral.Complete()`** must always be called (both paths) to release the navigation pipeline.
- Check `args.Source == ShellNavigationSource.Pop` so the guard only fires on *back* navigation, not forward pushes.
